---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import Masthead from "../components/Masthead.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---
<Base title="Contribute · OpenResearch">
  <main class="max-w-[1080px] mx-auto px-6 pt-8">
    <Masthead active="contribute" />
    <article class="cwrap">
      <h1 class="font-display">Publish in under 15 minutes</h1>
      <p class="lede">Everything on this site is a markdown file merged through a pull request.
        Pick a tier, copy its template, and open a PR — mechanical CI is the only gate.</p>

      <h2 class="caps" style="color: var(--oxblood)">Pick a tier</h2>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Tier</th><th>What it is</th><th>Required sections</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><b>Finding</b></td><td>One page, one measured result</td><td>Summary · Context · Technique · Evidence · How to replicate</td></tr>
          <tr><td><b>Technical report</b></td><td>Long-form study</td><td>Abstract · Background · Method · Results · Discussion · How to replicate</td></tr>
          <tr><td><b>Research paper</b></td><td>Full paper with related work and pre-registered metrics</td><td>Abstract · Introduction · Related work · Method · Results · Discussion · Conclusion · How to replicate</td></tr>
          <tr><td><b>Tutorial</b></td><td>Hands-on walkthrough</td><td>You'll need · You'll build · Steps · Wrap-up</td></tr>
          <tr><td><b>Note</b></td><td>One useful observation</td><td>Freeform, 100+ characters</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 class="caps" style="color: var(--oxblood)">The flow</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>Copy the template from <code>content/templates/&lt;tier&gt;.md</code> into
            <code>content/contributions/&lt;your-slug&gt;/index.md</code> (slug = the <code>id</code> field).</li>
        <li>Add a <code>bundle/</code> directory with a README if others should be able to replicate it.</li>
        <li>Run <code>npm run validate</code> locally — CI runs exactly the same checks.</li>
        <li>Open a PR. Merge = published; git history is your attribution and versioning.</li>
      </ol>

      <p>From M3, the <a href="/toolkit">toolkit</a> automates all of this: a
        <code>publish</code> skill turns a braindump into a formatted, validated PR.</p>
    </article>
    <Footer />
  </main>
</Base>
<style>
  .cwrap { max-width: 68ch; padding-top: 40px; }
  .cwrap h1 { font-weight: 600; font-size: clamp(28px, 4vw, 40px); margin: 0 0 12px; }
  .lede { font-family: var(--font-display); font-style: italic; font-weight: 500;
          font-size: 18px; color: var(--ink); margin: 0 0 28px; }
  .cwrap h2 { margin: 30px 0 12px; }
  table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 14px; display: block; overflow-x: auto; }
  th, td { border: 1px solid var(--hairline); padding: 8px 14px; text-align: left; }
  th { font-family: system-ui, sans-serif; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: .12em;
       text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--slate); }
  ol { padding-left: 20px; } li { margin: 8px 0; max-width: 62ch; }
  code { font-family: ui-monospace, Consolas, monospace; font-size: .88em; background: var(--soft);
         border: 1px solid var(--hairline); border-radius: 4px; padding: 1px 5px; }
  a { color: var(--oxblood); }
</style>
